Czech Stocks: Erste Group, New World Resources Move in Prague

-- B y   K r y s t o f   C h a m o n i k o l a s
-- 
2011-09-14T15:37:41Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-14/czech-stocks-erste-group-new-world-resources-move-in-prague.html
The Czech Republic’s PX stock index
fell for a fourth day, sliding 0.1 percent to 945.3 at its 4:28
p.m. close in Prague.  The following were among the most active equities on the
Prague Stock Exchange today. Stock symbols follow company names.  Erste Group Bank AG (EBS)  , an Austrian lender, dropped
2.6 percent to 491 koruna, its fifth day of losses. European
bank stocks tumbled, led by Societe Generale SA, after Moody’s
Investors Service cut the French lender’s debt to Aa3 from Aa2
with a negative outlook because of its holdings of Greek debt.  New World Resources Plc (NWR CP) slid 2.3 percent to 149.5
koruna, after earlier tumbling as much as 5.9 percent. The Czech
Republic’s biggest coking-coal producer was cut to “sell” from
“hold” and had its share-price estimate lowered by 45 percent
to 142 koruna at UniCredit SpA.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Krystof Chamonikolas in Prague at 
 kchamonikola@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gavin Serkin at   gserkin@bloomberg.net  